deck: The girls experiment with different identities.
description:
Plot Summary

After spending the day reading comics, the Powerpuff Girls decide that they need to spice up their superhero identities, and become more like their idols. Bubbles becomes Harmony Bunny (pictured right), Buttercup becomes a Spawn-esque character named Spore, and Blossom tries out a Wonder Woman style character by the name of Liberty Belle. But when the mayor calls the girls to get rid of a monster who is terrorising the city, the flaws in their new identities are soon exposed.
name: Super Zeroes

deck: Bubbles adopts a baby whale.
description:
Plot Summary

Bubbles' caring nature gets her into trouble, when she her need to take care of animals goes a little too far. The Professor decides enough is enough when she takes in a baby whale and tries to raise it.
name: Helter Shelter

deck: Buttercup searches to find her unique superpower.
name: Nuthin' Special

deck: The girl take care of a talking dog.
description:
Plot Summary

After he is the only witness to a crime, a talking dog is placed into a special witness protection program, and the girl take him into their home. But he soon outstays his welcome when he won't stop talking, and says a lot of things that hurt their feelings.
name: Shut the Pup Up
I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future

deck: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks.
description:
Plot Summary

Mr Green is a substitute teacher who comes to teach temporarily at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten. Though he tries his best, the people around him treat him differently because they think he looks like a monster.
name: Substitute Creature

deck: A musical episode in which the Powerpuff girls got tired of fighting villains. They met a Gnome who gave up their powers as a ruler. The episode was originally going to be the finale but it got banned in the U.S.
description:
Plot

All the villains are wreaking havoc at Townsville. The Powerpuff girls attempted to defeat them but got tired. They wished of a day of peace, love and understanding in Townsville. A Gnome gave the girls a deal: Give up your powers so the city will be fixed. The girls agreed on the deal. The Gnome talked to The Elders of Earth and Sea to cleanse villainy so the girls can become normal. The Gnome later took control of Townsville. The Professor warned the girls that the Gnome is against freedom. The girls made a discussion to the Gnome about opposites. The Gnome dissolves and the girls got their powers back. The girls say to the Townsville citizens to be themselves and have equal rights. They said it takes all kind people to make the world go round. The girls say to all the villains, "Why can't we all get along?" The villains agreed.

Songs

  • Townsville's Going Down
  • Rain
  • Give Up Your Powers
  • Normal Little Girls
  • Hear Me Fathers
  • Sunshine Down On Me
  • Best Day of My Life
  • Freedom Beef
  • Real Good
  • Why Can't We All Get Along?
name: See Me, Feel Me, Gnomey

deck: A clip show in which the flashbacks are almost entirely fictional.
description:
Plot Summary

The girls spend this episode reminiscing about past adventures, in standard television clip show style. But the difference is that their "memories" are mostly of events which have never occurred on the show. Examples include the girls being turned into babies, and traveling through time to see how they might live as teenagers.
name: The City of Clipsville

deck: Anakin chases a mysterious rogue pilot, against his masters orders.
name: Chapter 11

deck: Anarky returns to Gotham City and steals from the League of Assassins and pins it on Batman! He dosen't understand the forces he is dealing with.
description: Anarky returns once again to challenge Batman – but this time, his plan is far more deadly. Stealing a valuable object from the League of Assassins, Anarky pins the blame on Batman. At the same time, Anarky informs Batman that he knows where he can find the League. Although he knows it’s a trap, Batman goes with Katana anyway. As it turns out, Anarky has led both Batman, Katana, League leader Lady Shiva and her ninja assassins to a building that handles rare and deadly diseases. Once inside, Anarky releases one of the airborne viruses in the building. Now Batman and the others have to find a way to escape before being killed. One more thing: if the virus gets out…Gotham is doomed!
name: Sacrifice
